Peggy Bryan https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peggy_Bryan 0 Margaret Eileen "Peggy" Bryan (3 January 1916 – 12 January 1996) was an English film and stage actress, born in Birmingham, England. She appeared in many films, including most notably as the screen wife of George Formby in the comedy film Turned Out Nice Again (1941). She married cinematographer Wilkie Cooper, with whom she had three sons.
